recipes.name: Avocado White Bean Sandwich
ingredients: 1, 15 oz can cannellini beans, rinsed and drained
3, quartered marinated artichoke hearts plus more as desired, roughly chopped
Zest and juice of one small lime or lemon
1 chili pepper or 1/2 a deseeded jalapeno, finely chopped (optional)
1 clove garlic, crushed or finely minced

recipes.name: Bagels
ingredients: 1 cup  sourdough starter  ((218 grams of active and bubbly starter))
560 grams hard white wheat berries ((about 4 cups of freshly milled flour))

recipes.name: Baked Salad: Salsa Macha
ingredients: 2  New Mexican chilis (stems and seeds removed)
2-3  Chipotle Morita chilis (stems and seeds removed)
1  large Ancho chili (stem and seeds removed)
1 teaspoon Diamond Crystal kosher salt (use half if using Morton's)

recipes.name: Bean Steak Salad
ingredients: 1 lb of flank or bavette steak (you can do up to 1 1/2 lbs, butcher cuts can be inconsistent but this recipe is very forgiving!)
1 ball of fresh burrata to serve
2 tbs balsamic vinegar (I used fig balsamic and it was really good)

recipes.name: Beef Bourguignon
ingredients: 3 pounds beef brisket (trimmed of fat, chuck steak or stewing beef cut into 2-inch chunks)
3 cups red wine (like Merlot, Pinot Noir, or a Chianti - for a milder sauce, use only 2 cups of wine)
2-3 cups beef stock ((if using 2 cups of wine, use 3 cups beef stock))
1 pound white mushrooms (fresh, small or brown mushrooms ,quartered)

recipes.name: Beef Empanadas
ingredients: 2 small red bell peppers, seeded, chopped
1½ cups low-sodium chicken stock or broth
3 packages (12 each) Puff Pastry Dough for Turnovers/Empanadas (preferably Goya)
½ cup pitted green olives (Picholine or Spanish), rinsed well, cut in half lengthwise, divided

recipes.name: Blueberry Corn and Avocado Chopped Salad
ingredients: 1 large avocado, peeled, pitted and diced

recipes.name: Blueberry Scones
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour, plus more for dusting
1⅓ cups plus 1 Tbsp. chilled heavy cream

recipes.name: Broccoli Salad
ingredients: 7 cups chopped broccoli  ((~2 small heads broccoli as recipe is written))
1/2 cup roasted salted sunflower seeds  ((or sub other salted nut of choice))
1/2 cup finely diced red onion or shallot
1/4 cup dried cranberries or currants  ((unsweetened // or sub chopped pitted dates))
1/2 tsp sea salt  ((plus more to taste))
1 pinch black pepper  ((plus more to taste))

recipes.name: Brussel Sprout Salad
ingredients: 3/4 cup dry white or tricolor quinoa
6 ounces shredded curly or tuscan kale (about packed 4 cups)

recipes.name: Butternut Squash and Brussels Miso Bowl
ingredients: 2 cups baby spinach  ((or other leafy green))
1/2 batch Roasted Butternut Squash ((no curry powder // as recipe is written, ~3.5 cups cubed butternut squash))
2 ½ cups Brussels sprouts, browned outer leaves removed, large stalks trimmed off, halved ((quartered if very large in size))
1 tsp avocado oil ((or other neutral-flavored cooking fat that can withstand high heat))
1 healthy pinch  sea salt and black pepper
3 medium cloves garlic, skin removed and smashed or roughly chopped
1 Tbsp rice vinegar ((or sub apple cider or white wine vinegar))
2 cloves garlic  ((use less for less intense garlic flavor))

recipes.name: Butternut Squash Curry
ingredients: 1 ½-2 pounds sugar pie pumpkin or butternut squash, cut into ¾-inch pieces (about 4 cups) or 2 (14-ounce) cans pumpkin puree
1 ½ pounds boneless skinless chicken breast

recipes.name: Butternut Squash Nourish Bowl
ingredients: 2 cups baby spinach  ((or other leafy green))
1/2 batch Roasted Butternut Squash ((no curry powder // as recipe is written, ~3.5 cups cubed butternut squash))
2 ½ cups Brussels sprouts, browned outer leaves removed, large stalks trimmed off, halved ((quartered if very large in size))
1 tsp avocado oil ((or other neutral-flavored cooking fat that can withstand high heat))
1 healthy pinch  sea salt and black pepper
3 medium cloves garlic, skin removed and smashed or roughly chopped
1 Tbsp rice vinegar ((or sub apple cider or white wine vinegar))
2 cloves garlic  ((use less for less intense garlic flavor))

recipes.name: Carne Asada
ingredients: coarse sea salt and black pepper, to taste

recipes.name: Cashew Chicken
ingredients: 1 1/2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken breasts, ( cut into 1-inch cubes)
8  scallions (sliced, white and green parts separated)

recipes.name: Cashew Crunch Salad with Sesame Dressing
ingredients: 1/2 head of green cabbage, finely shredded
1/2 head of purple cabbage, finely shredded
chicken, shrimp, or any other protein you like
1/4 cup olive oil (you can use any other oil as well)
2 tablespoons sesame oil – very important for flavor!
a few shakes of garlic powder
optional: 1/4 cup Greek yogurt or mayo (more or less to taste – this changes it from a vinaigrette to more of a creamy dressing)

recipes.name: Chicken Dutch Oven Dates and Lemon
Chicken Wonton
ingredients: one 12-ounce bag frozen wontons (I like the mini chicken cilantro ones from Trader Joe’s or Costco)
1-2 cups chicken broth (depending on how soupy you like it)

recipes.name: Chickpea and Eggplant Curry
ingredients: 2 large tomatoes, grated on a large grate, with juices reserved
1¼ pounds eggplant, cut into ½-inch cubes (about 5 cups)
1 15-ounce can chickpeas, drained, rinsed, or 1¼ cups drained cooked chickpeas
1 tablespoon fresh lime juice, plus more
¼ cup coarsely chopped cilantro leaves

recipes.name: Chickpea Chopped Kale Salad Adobo Dressing
ingredients: 1 15-ounce can chickpeas  ((rinsed, drained, and thoroughly dried))
2 ½ - 3 Tbsp tandoori masala spice blend* ((see notes for DIY blend))
1/2 batch Candied Pecans  ((or other nuts of choice))

recipes.name: Chickpea/Roasted Red Pepper/Sun-Dried Tomato
ingredients: 1  15 oz. can of chickpeas (drained and rinsed)
1/2 tsp Diamond Crystal kosher salt (use half if using Morton's)
4  garlic cloves (finely grated with a microplane)
1 tbsp calabrian chili paste (or 1 tsp red pepper flakes)
4 cups dandelion greens (chopped, can be subbed for swiss chard or spinach)
Kosher salt and fresh cracked black pepper as needed
2 oz. ricotta salata (cut into thin slices)

recipes.name: Coconut Curry Salmon
ingredients: 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt (more for a larger filet)
2 tablespoons fish sauce or soy sauce
lots of lime juice and zest
cilantro, basil, mint, or other fresh herbs

recipes.name: Coconut Milk Poached Fish
ingredients: 4 cod loins or fillets (around 150g each), or any flaky white fish
2 lemongrass stalks, tough outer layer removed
2 x 400g tin good-quality coconut milk (ideally, at least 70% coconut extract)

recipes.name: Coconut Pineapple Shrimp Kebabs
ingredients: 4 teaspoons Tabasco Original Red Sauce (or hot sauce of choice)
1/4 cup freshly squeezed lime juice (from about 2 large limes)
1 pound large shrimp (31-40 count, peeled and deveined (you can use fresh or frozen, thawed shrimp))

1 cup (packed) cilantro leaves with tender stems
3 tablespoons olive oil, divided, plus more for drizzling
3 ears of corn, shucked, kernels removed

Crumbled feta, lime wedges, and cilantro (for serving)

recipes.name: Creamy Chipotle Beans
ingredients: 2 ears of corn, kernels cut away from the cob
1, 15 oz can pinto beans, drained and rinsed
1, 15 oz can cannellini beans, drained and rinsed
1 bell pepper (any color you like), diced
6 radishes, diced or cut into matchsticks
1/4 cup julienned sun-dried tomatoes (I used a the type in a jar packed in oil, drained)
3-4 chipotle peppers from a can packed in adobo sauce
1/4 tsp or more kosher salt to taste

recipes.name: Creamy Lemon Shrimp Pearl Couscous Scampi

1/2 tsp sea salt, more to taste
1 cup low sodium broth (I used bone broth)
1 can of lentils, drained and rinsed

recipes.name: Creamy Potato Leek Soup
ingredients: 12 oz yellow baby potatoes, roughly chopped
2 cans cannellini beans, drained and rinsed
5 cups good quality vegetable broth (I used reconstituted Vegetable Better Than Bouillon)

Kosher salt and fresh black pepper to taste

recipes.name: Creamy Wild Rice and Mushroom Soup

1 tablespoon soy sauce (GF soy sauce or tamari)
2 cooked chicken breasts, chopped or shredded

recipes.name: Curried Lentils

1-2 Tbsp olive oil ((optional // if avoiding oil, sub water))
2 Tbsp nut or seed of choice ((e.g. hemp seeds or roasted cashews // optional))

recipes.name: Curry Chicken Salad

½ medium apple with peel, diced

recipes.name: Dan Dan Pappardelle

ingredients: 1 1/2 cups loosely packed chopped dill (about 3 ounces), plus more for serving

recipes.name: Egg Roll in a Bowl

recipes.name: Garlicky Tomato Soup with Smashed White Beans

Finely chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley, for garnish

recipes.name: Spicy Wontons in Sauce
ingredients: one 12-ounce bag frozen wontons (I like the mini chicken cilantro ones from Trader Joe’s or Costco)
1-2 cups chicken broth (depending on how soupy you like it)

recipes.name: Summer Squash Lemon Thyme
ingredients: 1 tsp fresh lemon thyme leaves ((or normal thyme))

recipes.name: Sweet Pot Buddha Bowl
ingredients: 2 Tbsp olive, melted coconut, or avocado oil

recipes.name: Sweet Potatoes with Tahini Butter Chickpeas
Tagine
ingredients: 2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil, (plus more for drizzling)
3 cups peeled and finely diced butternut squash ((400g) (see Note 2))
1  big handful of flat-leaf parsley (or cilantro) leaves and tender stems,  (chopped)
¼ to ½ teaspoon cayenne pepper ((optional, ½ tsp for some good heat))
A generous crack of black pepper
2 teaspoons freshly squeezed lemon juice, (more to taste depending on your yogurt brand)

recipes.name: Teriyaki Crispy Chicken Rice Salad
ingredients: 2 Cups Cooked Rice (cooled - I use jasmine rice, but any rice should work well)
5  Persian Cucumbers (thinly sliced - you can also substitute one large English cucumber)
3 Tablespoons Soy Sauce or Coconut Aminos

recipes.name: Thai Chicken Soup
ingredients: 2 (~6 ounce each) chicken breasts  ((organic, pasture raised when possible // see vegan option in notes))
2 Tbsp coconut aminos or tamari  ((or soy sauce if not gluten-free))
1/2 cup thinly sliced shallot  ((mince if you prefer a finer texture))
4 Tbsp green curry paste  ((we like Thai Kitchen brand for store bought))
1 sprig lemongrass, trimmed and split in half
1/2 tsp sea salt, plus more to taste
1 fresh Thai chili, sliced at an angle  ((optional // omit for less heat))
1 box thin rice noodles  ((we prefer Thai Kitchen brand) or white rice (or sub green peas for grain-free))

recipes.name: Thai Chicken Thighs Coconut Rice
ingredients: 1 1" piece ginger, peeled, finely grated, plus 3 peeled slices
⅓ cup coconut palm sugar or (packed) light brown sugar
2 Tbsp. extra-virgin olive oil, plus more for brushing
2 tsp. freshly ground black pepper, plus more
½ medium head of green cabbage, stem trimmed, sliced into 1"-thick wedges
½ tsp. Diamond Crystal or ¼ tsp. Morton kosher salt, plus more
1 cup white jasmine rice, rinsed until water runs clear
Cilantro leaves with tender stems and lime wedges (for serving)

recipes.name: Thai-Inspired Chicken Meatball Soup
ingredients: 1 large bunch cilantro, leaves and stems finely chopped, a few whole leaves reserved for serving
2 tablespoons vegetable or coconut oil, plus more as needed
1 tablespoon lime juice, plus lime wedges for serving
Steamed white or brown rice, for serving

recipes.name: Turkey Burgers
ingredients: 1/2 bunch flat-leaf spinach, thick stems removed, leaves chopped (about 4 cups)
12 slider buns or small dinner rolls, split, lightly toasted (for serving)
Mayonnaise, sliced red onion, and pickle slices (for serving)

recipes.name: Turmeric Rice
ingredients: 2 cups uncooked jasmine rice (basmati works well too)
½ teaspoon ground black pepper (to taste)

recipes.name: Veggie Black Bean Burritos
ingredients: 1 can of black beans, rinsed (15 oz)
1/2 cup shredded cheese of choice, like cheddar or mozzarella
1/3 cup red onion, diced (about 1/3 of a large onion)

recipes.name: Veggie Shepherd's Pie
ingredients: 3 shallots, minced (or some onions and garlic)
1 teaspoon salt (more or less to taste)

recipes.name: Warm Fall Pearl Couscous Salad
ingredients: Chopped herbs (Highly recommend dill here, chives, parsley, basil)

recipes.name: Warm kale and Brussels sprouts with strawberries
White Bean Sausage Skillet
ingredients: 12 to 14 ounces smoked or Italian sausage, sliced ¼-inch thick
2 (15-ounce) cans white beans, such as great northern, butter beans, or cannellini, drained and rinsed
¼ teaspoon freshly cracked black pepper
½ bunch curly kale, stemmed, and torn into bite-size pieces (about 3 cups packed)
½ cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese, plus extra for serving

recipes.name: Zucchini Fritters
ingredients: 2 cups shredded zucchini  ((~2 small zucchinis as recipe is written))
2 Tbsp avocado or coconut oil, plus more for cooking
1 healthy pinch each sea salt and black pepper
1/4 tsp sea salt, plus more to taste
1/2 cup gluten-free flour blend  ((plus more as needed))
